Name: Full Strokes
Description:
The objective is to throw the stick with effort and allow the stick to rebound back to its original position. 

Make sure your wrist is returning to its original position before the stick does, otherwise it will get in the way of the stickâ€™s natural rebound.
Directions:
1. 1 full stroke with right hand (RH), followed by 1 full stroke with left hand (LH). Repeat 16x, creating constant eighth notes.
2. 2 full strokes RH, 2 full strokes LH. Repeat 8x
3. 3 full strokes RH, 3 full strokes LH. Repeat 8x
4. 4 full strokes RH, 4 full strokes LH. Repeat 8x
5. 5 full strokes RH, 5 full strokes LH. Repeat 8x
6. 6 full strokes RH, 6 full strokes LH. Repeat 8x
7. Increase tempo by 5 bmp and repeat
Remember:
1. Go slow!
2. Strive for an even sound between both hands. 
3. If the stick falls out of your hand, that's okay. It means you are not gripping the stick too hard.

Name: Down Strokes
Description: The objective is to throw the stick with effort and only allow the stick to rebound at a height that is lower than the starting position. This stroke goes from high to low.
Directions:
1. 4 full strokes (eighth notes) followed by 1 downstroke (quarter note) x8
2. 2 full strokes followed by 1 downstroke
3. 1 full stroke followed by 1 downstroke
Remember: Aim to keep the sound of your down strokes as close as possible to the sound of your full strokes. Stay relaxed.

Name: Eighth Note to Triplets
Description: The objective is to confidently move between eighth notes and triplets while maintaining a strong pulse
Directions: Use the resource sheet provided to transition from eighth notes to triplets on a single surface, utilizing a single dynamic. If you have time, try doing this same exercise at a new dynamic and/or change up the surfaces you are playing on.
Remember: Although this exercise seems simple, focus on what each rate feels like in your body.
